      "description": "We study the role of the Serre functor in the theory of derived equivalences.\nLet $\\mathcal{A}$ be an abelian category and let $(\\mathcal{U}, \\mathcal{V})$\nbe a $t$-structure on the bounded derived category $D^b \\mathcal{A}$ with heart\n$\\mathcal{H}$. We investigate when the natural embedding $\\mathcal{H} \\to D^b\n\\mathcal{A}$ can be extended to a triangle equivalence $D^b \\mathcal{H} \\to D^b\n\\mathcal{A}$. Our focus of study is the case where $\\mathcal{A}$ is the\ncategory of finite-dimensional modules over a finite-dimensional hereditary\nalgebra. In this case, we prove that such an extension exists if and only if\nthe $t$-structure is bounded and the aisle $\\mathcal{U}$ of the $t$-structure\nis closed under the Serre functor.Comment: As accepted by Advances in Mathematics; some differences in label and\n  page numbering may occur between this version and the published versio",
